  "response": "The time it takes for teeth to shift after a broken retainer varies depending on several factors:\n\n1. Individual factors:\n- Age\n- Genetics\n- Original orthodontic treatment\n- Tooth alignment before treatment\n\n2. General timeline:\n- Minor shifting can start within days\n- Noticeable movement typically occurs within 1-2 weeks\n- Significant movement can happen within 1-3 months\n- Full relapse varies but can occur within 6-12 months\n\n3. Recommendations:\n- Contact orthodontist immediately\n- Get retainer replaced as soon as possible\n- Wear new retainer consistently\n- Potentially use additional orthodontic intervention if significant shifting occurs\n\nThe precise timeline is different for each person, so professional consultation is recommended.",
